  "local_port": 47358,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I get into the Australian National University?",
  "response": "Getting into the Australian National University (ANU) requires careful preparation and meeting specific academic and application requirements. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you navigate the process:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Choose Your Program**\n   - Visit the ANU website to explore the courses and programs available.\n   - Decide on the program that aligns with your academic interests and career goals.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Check Entry Requirements**\n   **For Undergraduate Programs:**\n   - Academic Qualifications: Meet the minimum academic requirements for your chosen program (e.g., high school diploma, A-levels, IB, or equivalent).\n   - ATAR or Equivalent: ANU uses the Australian Tertiary Admission Rank (ATAR) for domestic students. International students must provide equivalent qualifications (e.g., SAT, ACT, or other standardized tests).\n   - English Proficiency: Non-native English speakers must provide proof of English proficiency (e.g., IELTS, TOEFL, or PTE).\n\n   **For Postgraduate Programs:**\n   - Bachelor\u2019s Degree: Hold a relevant undergraduate degree from a recognized institution.\n   - GPA: Meet the minimum Grade Point Average (GPA) requirement for your chosen program.\n   - Additional Requirements: Some programs may require work experience, portfolios, or entrance exams (e.g., GMAT for business programs).\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Prepare Your Application**\n   - **Undergraduate:** Domestic students apply through the Universities Admissions Centre (UAC). International students apply directly to ANU.\n   - **Postgraduate:** Apply directly through the ANU application portal.\n   - Required Documents:\n     - Academic transcripts.\n     - Proof of English proficiency.\n     - Resume/CV (for postgraduate programs).\n     - Personal statement or research proposal (if applicable).\n     - Letters of recommendation (if required).\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Submit Your Application**\n   - Check application deadlines for your program. ANU has different deadlines for domestic and international students.\n   - Pay the application fee (if applicable).\n   - Submit all required documents through the appropriate application portal.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Apply for Scholarships**\n   - ANU offers a range of scholarships for both domestic and international students. Check the ANU scholarships page and apply for any that match your eligibility.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Receive Your Offer**\n   - If your application is successful, you will receive an offer letter. Accept the offer and follow the instructions to enroll.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Apply for a Student Visa (International Students)**\n   - Once you accept your offer, apply for an Australian student visa (subclass 500).\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Prepare for Arrival**\n   - Organize accommodation (on-campus or off-campus).\n   - Attend orientation and familiarize yourself with ANU\u2019s resources and support services.\n\n---\n\n### Tips for Success:\n   - Research your program thoroughly and tailor your application to highlight your strengths.\n   - Apply early to increase your chances of securing a spot.\n   - Seek advice from ANU\u2019s admissions team or an education counselor if needed.\n\nGood luck with your application to ANU!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
